author: kfogel
msg: Fix issue #1744: Spurious warnings about commits spanning > 300 seconds.
(Commit.__init__): Set t_min higher.  It had been set to 1<<30,
which is halfway between the Unix Epoch and its expiration in
2038... A boundary we crossed on January 10th, 2004 :-), ahem.

author: kfogel
msg: Continue work on issue #1510 (default/vendor branch support):
Don't record a change when 1.1.1.1 is the same as 1.1.  This is the
optimization described in issue #1474, and completes r8611.
(Commit.add): Take new deltatext_code parameter, use it when
(Commit.commit): Use new deltatext code in determining whether or
not to emit a change for path.
(simple_tags): Undo the adjustment made in r8611, as expected.
